: Framework :
  ==========
-> Semi developed software  which provides common logics required for projects development.
-> Frameworks will help the developers to impliment more functionality in less time.
-> When we use framework to develop the project, we can focus only on bussiness logic.

Types of Framework
==================
1. Frontend Frameworks: To develop user interface in the project.
    Ex: Angular

2. Web Frameworks : To develop web layer in the project.
   Ex: Struts(Outdated)

3. ORM Frameworks : 
    Ex: Hibernate

=> By using Structs we can develop only web layer inn the project (Controllers)
=> By using hibernate we can develop only data access layer 



To overcome the Structs framework, Spring Framework comes into market.
==> Spring framework is called as Application Development Framework.
==> By using Spring framework we can develop end to end application.
==> Spring is free & open source framework
==> Spring framework developed in modular fashion .

Note: Spring frameworks means collection of modules.

====================
Spring modules
===================
1. spring core 
2.spring context
3.spring jdbc
4.spring orm
5.spring aop
6.spring web mvc
7.spring security
8.spring social
9.spring batch......

Note: Spring is very flexible framework. It will not force to use all the modules . Based on requirement we can pickup particular
module and we can use it .

==> Spring is versatile framework.(Easily it can be integrated with other frameworks).
